    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-01T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="422"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/187: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-01T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Department’s 26, June 30, 8 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] p.m.<note n="21"
                        xml:id="d422fn21">This telegram read as follows: “Please telegraph what, if
                        any, reaction the Foreign Office has shown with respect to the memorandum.”
                        (611.2531/187a)</note> Although the Minister of Foreign Affairs has assured
                    me in reply to my suggestions that the Foreign Office would endeavor to prepare
                    a reply to the Embassy’s memorandum of the 9th instant [<hi rend="italic"
                        >ultimo</hi>], I doubt if anything of much interest can be expected.</p>
                <p>I have been informed confidentially that it has been decided here to make every
                    effort to arrive at an understanding satisfactory to the United States but the
                    present attitude seems to indicate the intention to await the outcome of the
                    exploratory conversation by Señor García with the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
